.TH "LIGHTNING-PEER-SCORE" 1 "May 2026" "lightning 0.6.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
lightning-peer-score \- show weighted health score for one or all peers
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B lightning peer-score
.RI [ peer_id ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Without
.IR peer_id ,
returns the scored list for all peers (delegates to
.BR node-peers-score ).
With
.IR peer_id ,
returns the single entry for that peer or
.B {"error":"not_found"}
if the peer is unknown.
.PP
Output:
.nf
{"peer_id":..., "score":N, ...}
.fi
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Always.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR lightning-node-peers-score (1),
.BR lightning-peer-info (1)
